Terminalia
(Fig. 
13
): posterior margin of sternite 5 with a deeply excavated U-shaped median cleft (Fig. 
13
d
); lateral lobes of sternite apically rounded, with a vestiture of short setae along disc, 2x as long along caudal margin; basal section 1/2 the length of apical lobes. Cerci, in posterior view, sharply pointed and slightly medially separated and parallel, almost touching medially, with a few short setae on basal half (Fig. 
13
a
). In lateral view, curved and sharply tapered apically (Fig. 
13
b
). Surstylus well-developed, stout basally in lateral view, broadly rounded; in posterior view, basally enlarged and apically straight.
